OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778551406
OL,3,CEarly Easter adds to woe of retailers
OL,4,Csuffering from low consumer confidence
OL,6,FRetailers have suffered a
OL,7,Fdisappointing April as an early Easter
OL,8,Fcompounded stumbling consumer
OL,9,Fconfidence because of the Middle East
OL,10,Fcrisis, figures show.
OL,12,FTotal UK retail sales were down 3%
OL,13,Fyear on year, well below the 12-month
OL,14,Faverage growth of 1.8%, according to
OL,15,Fthe British Retail Consortium (BRC)
OL,16,Fand KPMG.
OL,18,FThis year's earlier Easter in March
OL,19,Fmeant food sales for April were
OL,20,Fdeceptively low in comparison with
OL,21,Flast year, down 2.5%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778551406
OL,3,CEarly Easter adds to woe of retailers
OL,4,Csuffering from low consumer confidence
OL,6,FBut non-food sales also decreased by
OL,7,F3.3%, below the 12-month average
OL,8,Fgrowth of 0.3%.
OL,10,FTaking March and April together, to
OL,11,Feven out the timing of Easter, total
OL,12,Fretail sales were up 1.5% year on year.
OL,14,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,15,Fsaid: "April's sales fall was largely
OL,16,Fdriven by the Easter shift, with food
OL,17,Fhit hardest. But weak consumer
OL,18,Fconfidence also played a role as fears
OL,19,Fabout the Middle East conflict driving
OL,20,Fup living costs led shoppers to rein
OL,21,Fin.
OL,26,@wD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778551406
OL,3,CEarly Easter adds to woe of retailers
OL,4,Csuffering from low consumer confidence
OL,6,F"Big-ticket purchases fell, with the
OL,7,Frecent recovery in furniture losing
OL,8,Fsteam, and uncertainty around summer
OL,9,Fholidays hitting discretionary spend.
OL,11,F"With the World Cup coming, retailers
OL,12,Fhope it will provide a lift, and early
OL,13,Fsigns show demand for TVs and sound
OL,14,Fsystems picking up."
OL,16,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,17,Fretail and leisure markets at KPMG,
OL,18,Fsaid:
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUvD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
