PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778551406
OL,3,CEarly Easter adds to woe of retailers
OL,4,Csuffering from low consumer confidence
OL,6,F"It was a disappointing April for the
OL,7,Fretail sector, even factoring in an
OL,8,Fearlier Easter shifting some spending
OL,9,Finto March. Bar marginal growth for
OL,10,Fbeauty, health and jewellery, retail
OL,11,Fsales fell across all other categories.
OL,13,F"Consumer confidence has been further
OL,14,Fdampened by rising prices due to the
OL,15,FIran conflict, with consumers cautious
OL,16,Fabout potential ongoing effects.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778551406
OL,3,CEarly Easter adds to woe of retailers
OL,4,Csuffering from low consumer confidence
OL,6,F"As a result, the retail sector is
OL,7,Ffacing a challenging start to spring/
OL,8,Fsummer, but there is hope that holiday
OL,9,Fdemand and the World Cup still manage
OL,10,Fto unlock spending in the weeks and
OL,11,Fmonths ahead."
OL,13,FSeparate figures from Barclays show
OL,14,Fconsumer card spending fell by 0.1%
OL,15,Fyear-on-year in April, the first fall
OL,16,Fsince November 2024.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@NO]
